, {\"sentence\": \"The buildings being used for the Olympics have eco-ambitions at the core.\", \"from\": 552, \"to\": 625, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The buildings\", \"from\": 552, \"to\": 565}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 581, \"to\": 593}, {\"ngram\": \"eco-ambitions\", \"from\": 599, \"to\": 612}, {\"ngram\": \"the core\", \"from\": 616, \"to\": 624}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Adidas Arena in northern Paris, which will host badminton and gymnastics, is made from low-carbon concrete and 80 percent of the building will be covered with greenery.\", \"from\": 626, \"to\": 798, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 630, \"end\": 636, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adidas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.421647592739147e-18, \"text\": \"Adidas\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adidas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adidas\"}, {\"begin\": 655, \"end\": 660, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999163265, \"rank\": 8.363097462137179e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"badminton\", \"from\": 678, \"to\": 687}, {\"ngram\": \"gymnastics\", \"from\": 692, \"to\": 702}, {\"ngram\": \"low-carbon concrete\", \"from\": 717, \"to\": 736}, {\"ngram\": \"80 percent\", \"from\": 741, \"to\": 751}, {\"ngram\": \"the building\", \"from\": 755, \"to\": 767}, {\"ngram\": \"greenery\", \"from\": 789, \"to\": 797}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u008c\\\"All the seats here are made of recycled materials,\\\" said the Arena's assistant event manager Julie Fabre, \\\"there are solar panels on the roof, there is lots of greenery as well for the ecological aspect, and so there you have it, the building was conceived to be eco-responsible.\\\"\", \"from\": 800, \"to\": 1084, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u008c\\\"All the seats\", \"from\": 800, \"to\": 817}, {\"ngram\": \"recycled materials\", \"from\": 835, \"to\": 853}, {\"ngram\": \"the Arena's assistant event manager Julie Fabre\", \"from\": 861, \"to\": 908}, {\"ngram\": \"solar panels\", \"from\": 921, \"to\": 933}, {\"ngram\": \"the roof\", \"from\": 937, \"to\": 945}, {\"ngram\": \"lots\", \"from\": 956, \"to\": 960}, {\"ngram\": \"greenery\", \"from\": 964, \"to\": 972}, {\"ngram\": \"the ecological aspect\", \"from\": 985, \"to\": 1006}, {\"ngram\": \"the building\", \"from\": 1034, \"to\": 1046}, {\"ngram\": \"eco\", \"from\": 1067, \"to\": 1070}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Aquatics Center is very eco.\", \"from\": 1086, \"to\": 1118, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Aquatics Center\", \"from\": 1086, \"to\": 1105}, {\"ngram\": \"very eco\", \"from\": 1109, \"to\": 1117}]}, {\"sentence\": \"/Paris 2024/MPG/Proloog The new Aquatics Center is the only permanent arena purpose-built for the Games.\", \"from\": 1119, \"to\": 1224, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"/Paris\", \"from\": 1119, \"to\": 1125}, {\"ngram\": \"The new Aquatics Center\", \"from\": 1143, \"to\": 1166}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1213, \"to\": 1222}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The architects were keen to ensure construction was as environmentally friendly as possible.\", \"from\": 1225, \"to\": 1317, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The architects\", \"from\": 1225, \"to\": 1239}, {\"ngram\": \"construction\", \"from\": 1260, \"to\": 1272}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They used wood and recycled materials \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 and the water in the center is warmed by capturing the heat output from a nearby data center.\", \"from\": 1318, \"to\": 1453, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"wood\", \"from\": 1328, \"to\": 1332}, {\"ngram\": \"recycled materials\", \"from\": 1337, \"to\": 1355}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093\", \"from\": 1356, \"to\": 1359}, {\"ngram\": \"the water\", \"from\": 1364, \"to\": 1373}, {\"ngram\": \"the center\", \"from\": 1377, \"to\": 1387}, {\"ngram\": \"the heat output\", \"from\": 1411, \"to\": 1426}, {\"ngram\": \"a nearby data center\", \"from\": 1432, \"to\": 1452}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u008c\\\"I think for me the most important thing was to answer to sustainability and all technical points we had to reach but with beauty and architecture,\\\" said Laure Meriaud, one of the architects who designed the Olympic Aquatics Center.\", \"from\": 1455, \"to\": 1690, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the most important thing\", \"from\": 1474, \"to\": 1498}, {\"ngram\": \"sustainability\", \"from\": 1516, \"to\": 1530}, {\"ngram\": \"beauty\", \"from\": 1581, \"to\": 1587}, {\"ngram\": \"architecture\", \"from\": 1592, \"to\": 1604}, {\"ngram\": \"Laure Meriaud\", \"from\": 1612, \"to\": 1625}, {\"ngram\": \"the architects\", \"from\": 1634, \"to\": 1648}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Aquatics Center\", \"from\": 1662, \"to\": 1689}]}, {\"sentence\": \"READ MORE Solar cars and tyre dust: Auto's future at Goodwood Festival of Speed Mackerel getting Norwegian fishermen out of deep water The UK village that inspired the Olympic Games \\u00e2\\u0080\\u008cParis 2024's ecological ambitions are not limited to this summer.\", \"from\": 1692, \"to\": 1946, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1791, \"end\": 1800, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway\", \"score\": 0.987646062282285, \"rank\": 0.012500482169204897, \"text\": \"Norwegian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway\"}, {\"begin\": 1834, \"end\": 1836, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999998291759912, \"rank\": 9.447095983030294e-08, \"text\": \"UK\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.o